.Dd March 6, 2026
.Dt pam_keybag 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm pam_keybag
.Nd authenticate with MobileKeyBag device passcode
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Op Ar service-name
.Ar function-class
.Ar control-flag
pam_keybag
.Op Ar options
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
module supports the
.Dq auth
function class.
It reads
.Xr PAM_AUTHTOK 3
and validates it through keybag logic implemented in
.Nm
itself.
By default, a dedicated signed helper process is used as a transport layer.
The module launches the helper with
.Fn posix_spawn 2
and sends passcode bytes over stdin; the helper loads
.Pa pam_keybag.so
with
.Fn dlopen 3
and calls exported module functions via
.Fn dlsym 3 .
.Pp
This is a private API path and may require platform-specific privileges.
If the helper cannot access the framework or symbol,
.Nm
returns
.Dv PAM_IGNORE .
.Pp
By default, the module does not call
.Fn MKBUnlockDevice ,
so successful authentication does not require triggering the SpringBoard unlock path.
.Pp
Remote authentication requests are denied by default; set
.Cm allow_remote
to enable this module for remote sessions.
.Pp
The following options may be passed to this authentication module:
.Bl -tag -width 20n
.It Cm user Ns = Ns Ar name1,name2,...
Comma-separated allowlist of usernames.
Defaults to
.Dq mobile .
.It Cm prompt Ns = Ns Ar text
Custom terminal prompt passed to
.Xr pam_get_authtok 3 .
Defaults to
.Dq Mobile passcode: .
.It Cm use_first_pass
Require an existing
.Dv PAM_AUTHTOK
from an earlier module.
If missing or invalid, authentication fails without prompting.
.It Cm try_first_pass
Try existing
.Dv PAM_AUTHTOK
first.
If missing or invalid, prompt for token and retry.
.It Cm nullok
Allow empty token and pass it to MobileKeyBag verify/unlock API.
By default empty token is rejected.
.It Cm nullok_secure
Like
.Cm nullok ,
but only for local requests.
For remote requests this option has no effect.
.It Cm unlock_springboard
Use
.Fn MKBUnlockDevice .
Without this option, the module uses verify-only path
.Fn MKBVerifyPasswordWithContext .
.It Cm direct_mode
Disable helper usage and call keybag/UI APIs directly from
.Nm .
This requires the PAM client process to be signed with the required entitlements.
.It Cm allow_remote
Allow remote PAM requests (for example ssh).
.It Cm prefer_ui_prompt
In helper mode, launch UI helper in parallel with terminal prompt.
Authentication succeeds when either UI or terminal path succeeds.
In
.Cm direct_mode ,
run UI prompt directly in-module before terminal fallback.
.It Cm ui_helper Ns = Ns Ar path
Override helper executable path used for both keybag auth and optional UI prompt.
Defaults to
.Pa @UI_HELPER_DEFAULT_PATH@ .
.It Cm module_path Ns = Ns Ar path
Override module dylib path used by helper
.Fn dlopen 3 .
Defaults to
.Pa @MODULE_DEFAULT_PATH@ .
.It Cm ui_reason Ns = Ns Ar text
Reason string passed to UI helper.
If omitted, defaults to a ps-like line with process PID and full command line.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Default verify-only path (local only, user defaults to
.Dq mobile ) :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
auth    required    pam_keybag.so
account required    pam_unix.so
.Ed
.Pp
Enable UI prompt in parallel:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
auth    required    pam_keybag.so prefer_ui_prompt ui_reason="Authenticate to continue"
account required    pam_unix.so
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr pam.conf 5 ,
.Xr pam 8 ,
.Xr pam_get_authtok 3
